verbose_text: Additionally, urine loss of chloride and magnesium was inappropriately induced (fractional excretion of chloride; FECl : 2.07% and fractional excretion of magnesium; FEMg; 16.2% at the next day after admission), whereas urine calcium loss was not obvious at admission (urine calcium / creatinine ratio : 0.09 mg/mg at admission and 0.26 mg/mg on the next day).
